          <head>Sufi treatise by Jami</head>
          <msContents>
            <msItem>
              <author>
                <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key=""/>
                <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key=""/>
              </author>
              <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Mar&#x101;tib-i sittah</title>
              <title xml:lang="per">&#x645;&#x631;&#x627;&#x62A;&#x628; &#x633;&#x62A;&#x651;&#x647;</title>
              <title xml:lang="eng" type="desc">Sufi treatise by Jami</title>
              <note>
                <p>Abridged Persian translation and commentary of the treatise on
									six grades of existence according to the principles of Sufism,
									conventionally attributed to the great &#x1E62;&#x16B;f&#x12B; writer,
										<persName>&#x2BF;Abd al-Ra&#x1E25;m&#x101;n "J&#x101;m&#x12B;" Hirav&#x12B;</persName>
									(d. 898/1492). </p>
                <p>The unnamed commentator describes the work as the second of two
									attempts, the latest completed 22 Ramaz&#x324;&#x101;n [10]79/23 February
									1669. </p>
                <p>The volume appears to have been part of a larger collection of
									tractates, fragments of which end and begin at either end of
									this work. </p>
                <p>Dated colophon (f. 17v): completed by <persName>Mu&#x1E25;ammad
										&#x1E62;&#x101;diq</persName> on 15 Rab&#x12B;&#x2BF; al-S&#x332;&#x101;n&#x12B; 1080/12 September
									1669. </p>
                <p>Folios detached; stained and worm-eaten; lacking original
									binding; fragile. </p>
              </note>
              <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="">Persian</textLang>
            </msItem>
